Just ordered from Joseph's Dream Burger on Avenue M. The food was horrible, and after the experience speaking to the order taker we will never order from them again. We ordered a Shawarma sandwich with lamb burger and a baby chicken sandwich. The Shawarma was actually baby chicken and there was no burger. The baby chicken was OK on its own. The vegetables, lettuce and tomato on both sandwiches were wilted, and tasteless. The sandwiches  were wrapped in wax paper and leaked through the wax and the paper bags. one positive is we asked for the sauce on the side and they sent plenty of sauce. The only thing we enjoyed was the side order of coleslaw at four dollars. If this is how they deliver food I'm terrified of stepping into their shop. To top it off there was a six dollar delivery charge for only a few blocks away which we weren't advised of. To top it off my husband was sick to his stomach as were I within minutes of eating the food. Stay far away!
